<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="kicker">Frequently asked</p>
    <h2>Airport-specific.</h2>
    <div class="faq">
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">How do you know if my flight is delayed?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>From the flight number you share at booking, we track status via tracking services. If there is a delay the driver arrives at the new ETA — without a "waiting fee".</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Where exactly will I be met?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>In most cases — at the arrivals exit (your specific exit at FLN, GRU, CGH etc. depends on the flight). The exact meeting point and driver contact arrive an hour before landing.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">Can I make a stop on the way?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>Yes. Intermediate points — bank, office, restaurant — are stated at booking and built into the timing. Price and format are fixed in advance.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary class="faq-summary">What if I arrive with extra luggage or with children?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          <p>The vehicle class is selected to fit the luggage volume and number of passengers. Child seats — by request at booking.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

